description.narrative: As of end of November, 225,646 children (50% girls) suffering from SAM were admitted into UNICEF-supported community-based management of acute malnutrition (CMAM) programs, more than 90% of whom were discharged cured. With an increased target from 250,000 in the previous three years to 300,000 in 2019, UNICEF managed to mobilize more resources to secure the nutrition supply pipeline which resulted in zero stockout of nutrition supplies and ready-to-use therapeutic food (RUTF) and to provide essential drugs and kits for the management of acute malnutrition, resulting in achieving 69% of the target as of end of quarter three. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
